            "label": "Description",
            "type": "String",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature casts a spell that you have in your repertoire.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong> You have an unexpended spell slot you could use to cast the triggering spell.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>When a foe Casts a Spell you know and you can see its manifestations, you can use your own magic to disrupt it. You expend one of your spell slots to counter the triggering creature's casting of a spell that you have in your repertoire. You lose your spell slot as if you had cast the triggering spell. You then attempt to counteract the triggering spell (page 458).</p>\n<p><strong>Special</strong> This feat has the trait corresponding to the tradition of spells you cast (arcane, divine, natural, or occult).</p>"
